text: America is more divided than it's been
in a long time right everyone knows that
but what does that tell us about the
people who support Donald Trump and
Hillary Clinton if you look at a new
poll from Pew Research it says 81% of
Trump supporters say America is worse
off than it was 50 years ago not only
that but they say it's worse off for
people like themselves so with Trump
supporters who tend to be older white
males without a college education are
pining for America of the 1950s and 60s
now at in Clinton supporters only 19
percent say things are better off in
yesteryear and it makes sense right
those drawn most to Clinton women blacks
and Hispanics college grads may benefit
more from the country's social and
demographic changes but it's not like
Clinton supporters think everything's
fine you can learn more about what
divides the two camps by looking at what
they think are the country's big
problems so we'll start with two dots
Clinton supporters and Trump supporters
on immigration only 17% of Clinton
supporters think it's a problem compared
with 66 percent of Trump supporters then
they get a little closer on terrorism
and they actually agree the most on how
big a problem racial tensions are
although they probably disagree on the
solution to this but then you see that
by far Clinton supporters are more
worried about income inequality if you
combine the two camps just about half
think the next generation of Americans
are worse off so it seems pretty
depressing but for over 30 years Gallup
has been keeping track of whether people
are satisfied with the country's
direction
and look most of the time that number is
